{{ja-kanjitab|もろこし|yomi=k}}
{{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>ro<sub>2</sub> ko<sub>1</sub>si⟩}} → {{IPAfont|⟨moro<sub>2</sub>ko<sub>1</sub>si⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/morəkosi/}} → {{IPAchar|/morokoɕi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=もろこし|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (''c.'' 753 {{CE}}).

Originally a compound of {{m|ja|諸|tr=moro-|pos=prefix meaning "[[many]]"}} + {{m|ja|越|tr=koshi}}, the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||stem or continuative form}} of {{m|ja|越す|tr=kosu||to [[cross]] ([[over]])}},<ref name="DJR"/> by reinterpretation of {{ll|ja|訓読み|''kun''-reading}} {{m|ja||越|tr=koshi}} from {{ll|ja|音読み|''on''-reading}} of {{m|ja|越|tr=Etsu||{{w|Yue (state)|(state of) Yue}}}}.<ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref>

